# Converted from PHONY
description: "The following tests the use of a PHONY target. It makes sure that the rules under a target get executed even if a filename of the same name of the target exists in the directory."
details: "This makefile in this test declares the target clean to be a PHONY target. We then create a file named \"clean\" in the directory. Although this file exists, the rule under the target clean should still execute because of it's phony status."

[setup]
touch: EXAMPLE_FILE clean

[case]
makefile:

.PHONY : clean
all: ; @echo This makefile did not clean the dir ... good
clean: ; rm -f EXAMPLE_FILE clean
options: clean
answer: "rm -f EXAMPLE_FILE clean"
